[SN]TITLE[SN]
Moped crash: Lewis Crouch family 'touched' by tributes

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
The family of a teenager killed when a car collided with his moped say they have been touched by all the tributes.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Lewis Crouch, 16, died in the crash on Peafield Lane in Mansfield Woodhouse shortly after 22:00 on Friday.
His family described him as a "joy to have around" and said they were "still in shock".
Nottinghamshire Police have not given any details of the car's driver but said they believe a driver in another vehicle may have seen the collision.
Paying tribute to Lewis, his mum Cheryl Broughton, said: "He would walk into a room and brighten everybody's day.
"He found some way of making you smile."
